I am trying to import code from a 2020 project into VScode 2021.
We see the message about importing the project.
But the clicking the “IMPORT” button does nothing.
It is as if the IMPORT button isn’t even clickable.

Have had this happen on a number of projects.

Thanks for your help in advance.

This is a known issue right now, aiming to be fixed for the 2022 season. A workaround is to create a new project and manually copy any applicable code. Alternatively, you can bump the version in your build.gradle from 2020.X.X to 2021.3.1

I did try to use the 2021.3.1 still ran into the bug.
Question, If I have code from 2018 or 2019 do I have to bump this up one year at a time?
Ex: bump 2018 → 2019->2020->2021

If so, how do you get the 3rd party libraries to work with the different versions on the same computer.
CTRE seems to only work with the latest version.

You can only manually upgrade from 2020 to 2021. If you need to import older years, the easiest solution right now is just to create a new 2021 project, and just copy your source code into the new src folder. With the importer being broken, thats the option. (BTW thats all the importer does anyway, just automatically. So if the importer is ever broken you can always just create a new project and copy your source code in)
